[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has an opening hand, 15 points, and a 5-card \S suit. Unfortunately EAST beat her to 
the punch by opening 1\H.

But SOUTH should get into the bidding anyway, by Overcalling 1\S. This shows a good \S suit 
and somewhere between 9 and 16 points.

NORTH has 6 points. If SOUTH had actually OPENED 1\S, NORTH would be obligated to bid. But knowing that 
the Overcall will not be made with more than 16 points, NORTH just passes.}

