[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has an opening hand, 15 points and five \Ss. But EAST beat him to the punch, 
so he overcalls 1\S. 

NORTH has 11 points, and if SOUTH had opened she would make a Limit Raise to 3\S. 

But when replying to an Overcall, the strength needs to be a little higher. In Deal 1 it was OK to 
pass a 1\S Overcall with 6 points, here it is correct to just raise to 2\S with 11 points.

SOUTH actually has a strong Overcall so he bids 4\S.}

